CHEM 1411: INTRODUCTORY CHEMISTRY I LABORATORY, FALL 2025
Welcome to General Chemistry Lab! In this course, we strive to create an environment where every student feels safe learning, sharing, and collaborating. Human diversity is welcome and celebrated in all its forms. If at any time you feel unwelcomed or unsupported in your learning, please reach out to your TA or the instructor.
This course is an introduction to experimental chemistry,

See our syllabus here!
Important:

15/25 points: 4 problem sets to be completed in groups -- dates found in syllabus. We'll form groups during our second discussion section. Each problem set is worth 5 points, and your lowest grade out of the 4 problem sets will be dropped.
10/25 points: 12 weekly quizzes -- to be held at the end of each section. Each quiz is worth 1 point; get 2 out of 3 questions correct on 10/12 quizzes to score full points. Discussion attendance is important for this reason.
